From f827952a2985c2069c59d5698b27a4da6585fe64 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thiraviyam Mariyappan <tmariyap@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 13 Jul 2025 21:29:48 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:ath12k:DP: tx performance optimization

Below changes provides ~2gbps improvement in DBDC DL test. They are

1. In TX path currently checks ring full by reading TP on every packet.
The TP always follows HP and ring full is rare and do not occur for
every packet. So, introducing this API
ath12k_hal_srng_src_begin_get_next_entry_nolock_fast to remove the
volatile access of tp for every packet and fetch the real tp only
if ring full condition is hit with last cached tp.

2. Avoid taking locks while processing the tx. The rings are accessed
associated with specific cores for processing. There is no need to
take locks and lock held check to avoid contention. Introduce simple
inline functions to update the rings directly without too many
checks in the ath12k_hif_write32 access.

3. Disable the tcl_ring_retry feature, which is used to select the
next TCL ring when the current ring is full. This feature introduces
spin lock contention in the fast TX path, consuming CPU cycles and
potentially impacting KPIs. Therefore, this feature is removed to
simplify the TX code path and drop packets when the ring is full.

4. Precompute the datapath registers addresses in hp_addr_direct and
use it directly to save cpu time during tx completion.

Orginal patches:
718-d-ath12k-remove-locks-and-optimize-tx-completion-path.patch
720-h-ath12k-Avoid-register-address-caculations-on-a-per-p.patch
760-ath12k-Use-correct-offsets-for-handling-pci-and-ahb-.patch
999-QSDK-DP-wifi-ath12k-optimize-ring-full-condition-che.patch

Patch dependency:
